Subject: Re: [T2] Re: [WetWesties] Sink doesn't work - I tried the

Two things before you set off on a trip: Is it hooked to the fused side or the un-fused side of the fuse box? If removing the fuse where it is wired in causes a loss of power then you're probably (maybe) okay. What else is on that same fuse? If you know ahead what all is depending on that fuse, you'll know the first place to look if there is a problem - or what you might need to turn off when operating the sink! I suspect that the original inline fuse was wired to the hot side of the fusebox and the inline fuse was the only fuse and was not shared by anything else. Best to go back to that setup, IMHO. -BaH

-Dave "Busahaulic" Pearson (BaH)
