--- On Mon, 7/7/08, James Neumeister <boletivore(-at-)comcast.net> wrote:


 I got it solved, it seems like the wires weren't making
 contact inside the wire nuts on the short leads off the
 pump, I took them apart to run a wire from the fuse box to
 test to see if the pump was still good, after I hooked them
 back up it works great, there wasn't much stripped wire,
 that may have contributed.
 
 FWIW I do not have an inline fuse or a fuse at the pump on
 my '77, just a fuse in the regular fuse panel.
